Pallavi 🪷

In love with this pallavi collection from @silalankaraa 

Pallavi — a name like morning breeze,
Soft in her ways, yet strong with ease.
A heart so calm, a mind so clear,
She walks her path with no trace of fear.

Not loud, not lost in worldly race,
She moves with charm, with quiet grace.
She doesn’t follow — she leads with light,
With dreams held firm and eyes so bright.

Simple in soul, yet rare to find,
She’s the kind that leaves echoes behind.
Unique in thought, in how she stands,
Her life — a story written in her hands.

No need to prove, no masks to wear,
She knows her worth, she’s self-aware.
Confident, kind, a spirit so true —
Pallavi shines in all she’ll do.

Tirumalai Nayakar Mahal, Madurai🪷

Built in 1636 by King Tirumalai Nayak, this palace was once a grand royal residence under the Nayaka dynasty. Designed with a fusion of Dravidian, Islamic, and European styles, it features towering white pillars, arched corridors, and intricately painted ceilings.

	•	Only ¼ of the original palace remains—the rest was dismantled by his grandson.
	•	Hosts a light & sound show narrating the Tamil epic Silappatikaram.
	•	A popular film shooting location, seen in Bombay, Guru, and more.
